#X text 228 278 You can change the reference point. Note that 2 values set a region where the output is 1!, f 35;
#X text 253 422 amount (%);
#X msg 191 340 exp 1 -1;
#X msg 198 364 exp 1.5;
#X msg 212 387 exp 0;
#X text 268 340 You can also set exponential factors below and above the reference point(s). By default we have '0' (which linear and so is '1'). Negative values flips it vertically., f 48;
#X obj 487 542 keytrack~;
#X text 361 433 You can actually also set different amnount values below and above the reference point(s). Check the help file. This is quite a complex and versatile object. Take some time to study it. Note we also have a signal version., f 36;
